cabbage-tree hat
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a light-weight hat with a wide, upturned brim, made out of the leaves of the cabbage tree (orig. Aust.; ref. may be to hats imported from Aust.; or to those made locally from Cordyline (or nikau) leaves); ]cabbage hat; cady.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes:
