Source: Bidwill of Pihautea
Author: BIDWILL & WOODHOUSE
Vol / Page: 53
Edition:
Quote: The universal dress in those says [c1848] for country settlers and travellers was moleskin trousers, blue serge shirt, and that much prized head-covering, when it could be obtained, a New South Wales cabbage tree hat with a long black ribbon. [Note] A broad brimmed hat plaited from the  leaves of the Australian Cabbage Tree.
Notes: Pagination from 1927 edition

